description:
&lt;p&gt;Following the successful promotion of the current post holder we are looking to recruit a new team member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a qualified Speech and Language Therapist who is keen to develop their skills in community and acute adult speech and language therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small but perfectly formed team based at the James Paget University Hospital, providing both communication and dysphagia assessment and intervention across community and acute settings. This is an exciting time to join our team as we implement the use of video interventions, alongside other service developments. There will be a broad range of opportunities to develop your clinical skills, supported by regular supervision and a cohesive team approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work across Great Yarmouth and Waveney Localities and as a Social Enterprise place a huge amount of importance on collaborative working and have strong community focus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to know more about what we have to offer and how we work please do contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
